title: Cracked Tiles in Bathroom 4A - Replacement Required
description:
RFI #5: Tiles in bathroom 4a are cracked. Need to determine how to replace these without damaging the waterproofing.

Suggested approach: To replace the cracked tiles without damaging the waterproofing, follow these steps: 1. Carefully remove the grout around the cracked tiles using a grout saw or rotary tool. 2. Gently lift the cracked tiles using a chisel and hammer, taking care not to damage the underlying waterproofing membrane. 3. Clean the substrate and apply new waterproofing if necessary. 4. Install replacement tiles with appropriate adhesive and grout.

title: Roofing Design Issues Identified in A505 Office Roofing Details
description:
After reviewing the A505 Office Roofing Details, the following potential issues have been identified:

1. Spelling/Typographical Errors:
   - "APPRORPIATETERMINATION" instead of "APPROPRIATE TERMINATION" (appears multiple times)
   - "MUST EXTEND1/2"" should have a space after "EXTEND"

2. Technical Issues:
   - Detail #6 (EPDM Expansion Joint) shows compressible tube/insulation but doesn't specify material type or compression rating
   - Note #2 in Detail #6 mentions the compressible tube must exceed deck opening by 50% min., but doesn't clarify if this is diameter or width
   - Some fastener spacing is specified as "MAX." but minimum spacing requirements are not provided
   - Detail #8 (EPDM Roof Penetration) note #4 mentions additional field membrane securement when pipe diameter exceeds 18" but doesn't specify the method or pattern

3. Potential Water Issues:
   - Detail #9 (EPDM Thru-Wall Scupper) doesn't show overflow provisions or secondary drainage
   - No specific slope requirements are shown for the roof or at scupper locations
   - No ice/water shield or secondary membrane protection is specified at critical junctions

4. Missing Information:
   - No specific wind uplift criteria or design pressures
   - No fire rating specifications
   - No R-value specifications for insulation
   - No details for transitions between different roof areas or elevations

5. Constructability Concerns:
   - Some details may be difficult to properly execute in the field, particularly the corner details
   - Detail #8 requires hot stack penetration to be "free of all rust" which may be difficult to achieve and maintain long-term

Recommendation: Review these items with the design team and make necessary clarifications or corrections before proceeding with construction.

title: Technical Concerns in EPDM Roofing Details
description:
Technical issues identified in drawing A505 that require resolution:
- In the Expansion Joint detail (#6), there's insufficient information about the compressible tube sizing - note #2 states it "must exceed deck opening by 50% min" but doesn't specify maximum compression limits or proper installation guidelines
- The Thru-Wall Scupper detail (#9) shows potentially insufficient slope for proper drainage
- No clear specifications for minimum overlap requirements in several details

These issues could lead to performance problems and should be addressed before construction.
